### Project — agent-skills

# Local skill-evaluation workspaces (eval sets, optimization-loop reports,
# grader traces, etc.). Useful locally for pre-shipment audits; regenerated
# per audit run, not worth tracking — EXCEPT .eval/triggers/, the committed
# boundary corpus for kerby's own triggering (should-fire / should-not-fire).
# Manual regression checklist: feed to skill-creator's run_eval (or eyeball)
# when the SKILL.md description changes. No gate auto-runs it.
.eval/*
!.eval/triggers/

# Skill-creator iteration workspaces (per-skill eval traces, grader scripts,
# benchmark JSON, viewer HTML, run logs, packaged .skill bundles). Useful
# locally between iterations; not worth tracking in git history.
skills/*-workspace/

# Asset working directories — draft renders, mockups, archived hero
# versions, ad-hoc rendering scripts. Useful locally during banner / hero
# design iteration; the shipped art lives at assets/<name>.svg and
# assets/icons/<name>.svg.
assets/_archive/
assets/_drafts/

# Skill runtime output directories — generations, prompt-brief artifacts,
# smoke-test renders, pinned reference outputs. The skill's SKILL.md
# writes here at runtime (e.g., `pixel-art` writes
# `docs/pixel-art/<slug>-<date>.{png,webp,md,svg}`). Useful locally;
# not part of the shipped skill.
docs/pixel-art/

# whoami character-portrait review contact sheet — a local review aid,
# not part of the shipped skill. The shipped portraits are the 512×512
# skills/whoami/assets/characters/<class>.png files.
skills/whoami/assets/characters/_contact.png

# Obsidian vault config — local note-taking workspace over the repo.
# Per-user editor state, not part of the shipped plugin.
.obsidian/

# ghostwriter voice samples — real samples are personal data and live
# user-local (~/.claude/ghostwriter/), never in the repo. Belt-and-suspenders
# guard in case someone copies real messages next to the shipped templates.
skills/ghostwriter/references/samples-*.md
!skills/ghostwriter/references/samples-*.template.md

# impeccable plugin hook caches — per-directory `.impeccable/` dirs holding
# local session/hook cache + local config (hook.cache.json, config.local.json).
# The plugin manages its own entries in .git/info/exclude per directory, but
# that's local-only and misses nested dirs; this shared bare-name rule ignores
# `.impeccable/` at every depth for all contributors.
.impeccable/

# Python bytecode
__pycache__/
*.pyc
